\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 \strokec2 Re-Evaluating LMU & Nvidia (Thinking Mode Analysis)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 Le Mans Ultimate uses a modified rFactor 2 engine (DX11). Unlike modern DX12 titles, it is highly sensitive to single-thread CPU performance and GPU memory bus latency.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Nvidia Reflex:
\f0\b0  In LMU settings, set to 
\f1\b On + Boost
\f0\b0 . This forces the GPU to maintain higher clock speeds even during low-load scenarios (like long straights) and bypasses the Windows render queue.\
\ls15\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 G-Sync + V-Sync Combo:
\f0\b0  * 
\f1\b Nvidia App:
\f0\b0  V-Sync 
\f1\b On
\f0\b0 .\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl1
